PiperOrigin-RevId: 386419163
Change-Id: I385590ad3d852a654288afdd37697b653961578f","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/144413cd24c6efbf028fa568c4067087502f3de9"},{"sha":"f633cb5f5cc657149ae0b524163dd2d2b4b58b64","author":{"name":"Srishti Srivastava","email":"904a07f5d5a3adde1e4d458a4465bbe1e0df36dc@polymagelabs.com"},"message":"[MLIR][TF] Canonicalize tf.DivNoNan and tf.MulNoNan

Added and used a template to canonicalize tf.DivNoNan and tf.MulNoNan.
When the divisor/multiplier of tf.DivNoNan/tf.MulNoNan, respectively is
a constant with all the elements in its tensor (with float/complex type)
being zero, tf.DivNoNan/tf.MulNoNan is replaced with its
divisor/multiplier, respectively. Further, when the divisor/multiplier
of tf.DivNoNan/tf.MulNoNan, respectively is a constant with all the
elements in its tensor (with float/complex type) being non-zero,
tf.DivNoNan/tf.MulNoNan is replaced with tf.Div/tf.Mul, respectively.
Relevant test cases are added as well.

Signed-off-by: Srishti Srivastava <srishti.srivastava@polymagelabs.com>","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/f633cb5f5cc657149ae0b524163dd2d2b4b58b64"},{"sha":"91c414616cdaf70172e4a7e479f5bd6bbfda563e","author":{"name":"Tres Popp","email":"bb390cedfd91dd9be00fd9562bdc5562c5867450@google.com"},"message":"Internal change.
